data.description: If you’ve dreamt of morning fishing, coffee canalside, pool floating, Jacuzzi soaking, grilling outdoors, sunsets dockside, and fires in the evening with jasmine in the air, this TROPICAL OASIS is for you…from waterfront, to beach area, tiki hut, Koi ponds, to fruiting trees, this property has it all, ready to be enjoyed without you having to do a thing; truly! Carefully planned landscaping offers zoned areas of relaxation & entertainment between the large, HEATED, lap pool with oversized screened lanai, & the canal with dock & 10,000lb boat lift. RARE to find, this property boasts its own cemented boat ramp into the canal which can also have a boat house built upon...Vacation Rental, AirBNB increased potential as Sellers have long history of Seasonal & Short Term Renters in the main home. Eat fresh from the gardens full of herbs, pineapples, blueberries, bananas, papayas, & avocados, which are all watered via an irrigation system fed by an 80’ deep artisan well. Listen and watch the soothing waterflow from one pond to another along a connecting stream adorned with water plants. When you catch trout off your dock, or bring in snook from the harbor, cleaning it will be a breeze with the dock sink. Inside, you find lovely, easy-to-clean ceramic tile on diagonal, recessed lighting, beautifully tiled bathrooms, hardwood cabinetry with rainfall glass panels & specialty hardware in the kitchen, easy access laundry/office combo offering large pantry, built-in desk, plus loads of storage cabinets. Handy workshop in garage holds a spot for all your tools, plus conveniently has the door to the side yard, where you’ll find a 50 amp RV plug. Pool, Jacuzzi, & Tiki Bar all have a bonus, composting outdoor bathroom to utilize! Well maintained & manicured, home has new appliances, a 2018 A/C with heat pump, a 2013 Roof, 2017 pool heater, newly installed solar PHOTOVOLTAIC system ($45,000 value), HURRICANE protection, & kitchen RO system. Easy, 25 minute enjoyable ride out to open water. Charlotte Harbor is Florida’s largest unpolluted Estuary, 160 square miles of rolling sea-grass beds, clear, untainted water, and home to huge schools of sea trout, red drum, black tips, mackerel, and snook. The happiest place in Port Charlotte, you cannot help but relax, laugh, and soak in the pleasures of the tropics on this property. Live the Florida life, enjoying the outdoors year-round, in this idyllic, unique slice of paradise!
